    {"@type":"Question","name":"Why is spring a good time for a roof checkup?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Spring in Tampa Bay offers a critical window between winter's cooler, drier months and the summer rainy season. It's the ideal time to assess any damage from winter cold snaps, repair UV-degraded sealants, clear debris, and ensure your roof is prepared for the heavy afternoon thunderstorms that begin in May and the hurricane season that starts June 1."}},
    {"@type":"Question","name":"What does a spring roof checkup include?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"A spring checkup includes a full inspection of all roofing materials, flashing, sealants, gutters, soffit, fascia, and attic ventilation. We also clear debris, clean gutters, reseal any failed caulking, and repair minor damage. You receive a detailed report with photos documenting your roof's condition."}},
    {"@type":"Question","name":"Can winter weather in Tampa Bay damage my roof?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, even in Florida. Temperature fluctuations cause materials to expand and contract, loosening fasteners and cracking sealants. Cold snaps can make shingles brittle and more susceptible to cracking. Extended dry periods allow UV damage to accumulate without the protective moisture that rain provides. A spring checkup catches these issues."}},
    {"@type":"Question","name":"How much does a spring roof checkup cost?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Happy Roof offers free roof inspections as part of our spring checkup service. If maintenance work is needed beyond the inspection (gutter cleaning, sealant repair, minor fixes), we provide transparent pricing with no surprises. Many homeowners find that a small investment in spring maintenance saves thousands in avoided repairs later."}},
